[src:sturm-liouville-theory/eigenfunction] Note that in this case the eigenfunction is itself a function of its associated eigenvalue λ, which can take any real or complex value.
[src:sturm-liouville-theory/eigenfunction] In particular, note that for λ = 0 the eigenfunction *f*(*t*) is a constant.
