[src:sturm-liouville-theory/eigenfunction] where λ = 2 is the only eigenvalue of the differential equation that also satisfies the boundary condition.
[src:sturm-liouville-theory/eigenfunction] Eigenfunctions can be expressed as column vectors and linear operators can be expressed as matrices, although they may have infinite dimensions.
[src:sturm-liouville-theory/eigenfunction] As a result, many of the concepts related to eigenvectors of matrices carry over to the study of eigenfunctions.
